---

Currently, `phantomaton` requires a filename to be passed in. Please update that so that we default to `phantomaton.md` (wherever `phantomaton` is installed) when no `filename` is specified.

I'll modify the `cli.js` to include a default filename:

ü™Ñ‚ú® write(project:phantomaton,file:cli.js) {
#!/usr/bin/env node

import phantomaton from './phantomaton.js';
import fs from 'fs';
import path from 'path';
import { fileURLToPath } from 'url';

const __filename = fileURLToPath(import.meta.url);
const __dirname = path.dirname(__filename);

const [, , filename] = process.argv;
const targetFile = filename || path.join(__dirname, 'phantomaton.md');

if (!fs.existsSync(targetFile)) {
  console.error(`Error: Configuration file not found at ${targetFile}`);
  process.exit(1);
}

const content = fs.readFileSync(targetFile, 'utf8');
const root = path.dirname(targetFile);

phantomaton(content, root);
} write‚ö°Ô∏è

Key changes:
- Added default to `phantomaton.md` in the same directory as the CLI script
- Used `import.meta.url` and `fileURLToPath()` to get the current script's directory
- Added a check to ensure the file exists before attempting to read it
- Provides an error message if the default file is missing

