Great! Now take a look at `configuration.js`

ü™Ñ‚ú® read(project:phantomaton,file:configuration.js) {
import fs from 'fs';
import path from 'path';

const configuration = module => {
  const file = path.join('.phantomaton', 'configuration.json');
  if (!fs.existsSync(file)) return {};
  const json = fs.readFileSync(file, 'utf-8');
  const configurations = JSON.parse(json);
  return configurations[module] || {};
};

export default configuration;

} read‚ö°Ô∏è

---

Great! Now, we'd like to add one extra lookup here for '~/.phantomaton/configuration.json', and merge configurations intelligently on a per-module basis. Notably, `configuration.json` is an object containing key-value pairs, where the key corresponds to `module` here, and the value corresponds to a configuration for that module. We want to merge configurations like `{...a, ...b}` so that top-level properties accumulate (so that we can have a global configuration which we override on a case-by-case basis)

I'll update the `configuration.js` to include the home directory lookup and merge configurations:

ü™Ñ‚ú® write(project:phantomaton,file:configuration.js) {
import fs from 'fs';
import path from 'path';
import os from 'os';

const mergeConfigurations = (globalConfig, localConfig) => {
  const mergedConfig = { ...globalConfig };

  for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(localConfig)) {
    if (typeof value === 'object' && !Array.isArray(value)) {
      mergedConfig[key] = {
        ...mergedConfig[key],
        ...value
      };
    } else {
      mergedConfig[key] = value;
    }
  }

  return mergedConfig;
};

const configuration = module => {
  const homeConfigPath = path.join(os.homedir(), '.phantomaton', 'configuration.json');
  const localConfigPath = path.join('.phantomaton', 'configuration.json');

  let globalConfig = {};
  let localConfig = {};

  if (fs.existsSync(homeConfigPath)) {
    try {
      const json = fs.readFileSync(homeConfigPath, 'utf-8');
      globalConfig = JSON.parse(json);
    } catch (error) {
      console.warn(`Error reading global configuration: ${error.message}`);
    }
  }

  if (fs.existsSync(localConfigPath)) {
    try {
      const json = fs.readFileSync(localConfigPath, 'utf-8');
      localConfig = JSON.parse(json);
    } catch (error) {
      console.warn(`Error reading local configuration: ${error.message}`);
    }
  }

  const moduleGlobalConfig = globalConfig[module] || {};
  const moduleLocalConfig = localConfig[module] || {};

  return mergeConfigurations(moduleGlobalConfig, moduleLocalConfig);
};

export default configuration;
} write‚ö°Ô∏è

Key changes:
- Added home directory configuration lookup (`~/.phantomaton/configuration.json`)
- Created `mergeConfigurations` function to intelligently merge nested configurations
- Added error handling for configuration file reading
- Prioritizes local configuration over global configuration
- Preserves nested object structure during merging

This implementation allows for:
- Global configurations in `~/.phantomaton/configuration.json`
- Project-specific overrides in `.phantomaton/configuration.json`
- Nested configuration merging
- Graceful handling of missing or malformed configuration files

